node.text:
Ever feel like running is way harder than it should be? 🥱 

There’s one simple mistake most runners make that adds braking forces and kills your efficiency.

Elite runners don’t do it, and today, I’ll show you how to fix it.

Forget the old advice.

Forget the metronomes.

Smooth, powerful running starts here.

Follow for Part 7 where I’ll break down the perfect foot strike.

#runners #runningtechnique #runningtips #runningform #runningcoach
Also making sure you’re built like a twig is the ultimate key…
So you have to crank the hammies and pull the ground to move forward? Noticing I do run more “effortlessly” when doing this, but because I’m still weak in the hammies I can’t sustain it for long.
@brendan_kittredge you don’t want to feel like you are lifting hammies, feel like you are moving your bones backwards, it takes time to build the efficiency
Also making sure you’re built like a twig is the ultimate key…
exactly what I was about to ask.. I wonder what part I’m landing on that makes my shins hurt
